The paper deals with a problem of clustering a graph into two communities based on observed vertex correlations, which is a problem in information theory (cs.IT) and data mining (cs.DM). The paper also proposes an efficient recovery algorithm based on semidefinite programming, which falls under the category of optimization (cs.NA). The problem of community detection is a popular topic in machine learning (cs.LG) and the paper discusses the stochastic block model, which is a common model in statistical inference (cs.SI).
